

        --------------------------------------------------------------
        README for ~4Dgifts/examples/Fortran/globe source code example
        --------------------------------------------------------------

    globe displays a user-manipulatable globe using a converted earth-
    centered world coordinate data base.

    Manipulating the globe is done via the following sequences when the
    mouse cursor is within the boundaries of the globe window:

    ONEKEY:  moving the mouse horizontally will translate the globe 
	     towards or away from the viewers eye. 

    TWOKEY:  moving the mouse will translate the globe in the direction
	     the mouse moves.

    THREEKEY:  moving the mouse will rotate the globe.  
